title: New York Times Best Sellers 08 September 2013 New Fiction (MOBI+
description:
New York Times Best Sellers New Fiction  08 September 2013 (MOBI+Epub)


New York Times Best sellers - Fiction

The New York Times best selling Fiction print/eBook of September 08, 2013

This weeks New editions (3, 8, 9, 10, 11, 17, 18, 20, 24)

1 - THE CUCKOO'S CALLING - Robert Galbraith
The struggling detective Cormoran Strike investigates a supermodel s suicide; by J.K. Rowling, writing pseudonymously.
2- THE HUSBAND'S SECRET - Liane Moriarty
A woman reads a letter from her husband, very much alive, that was intended to be opened only after his death.
3 - WICKED FIRSTS - Elisabeth Naughton and others
Six stories of first loves and first times.
4 - MISTRESS - James Patterson and David Ellis
When he begins to investigate a friend s mysterious death, a man discovers that she was leading a double life.
5 - HIGH HEAT - Lee Child
With New York City blacked out, a 16-year-old Jack Reacher helps a woman with a problem; a Jack Reacher novella.
6 - THE SILENT WIFE - A. S. A. Harrison
Told in alternating voices, this is a chilling portrait of a marriage gone terribly awry.
7 - INFERNO - Dan Brown
The symbologist Robert Langdon, on the run in Florence, must decipher a series of codes created by a Dante-loving scientist.
8 - NIGHT FILM - Marisha Pessl
Investigators pursue a master horror film auteur after his daughter is found dead.
9 - THE BONE SEASON - Samantha Shannon
A young clairvoyant discovers her powers in a dystopian England in 2059; the first pick of the  Today  show book club.
10 - UNLOCKED - Maya Cross
The conclusion of the Alpha Group trilogy.
Bonus: Book 1 - Locked & Book 2 - Unlocked
11 - THE THIRD KINGDOM - Terry Goodkind
A sequel to  The Omen Machine.  
Bonus: The Omen Machine
12 - AND THE MOUNTAINS ECHOED - Khaled Hosseini
A multigenerational family saga centers on a brother and sister born in Afghanistan; from the author of  The Kite Runner.  
13 - GONE GIRL - Gillian Flynn
A woman disappears on the day of her fifth anniversary; is her husband a killer?
14 - ENDER'S GAME - Orson Scott Card
Government agencies breed child geniuses and train them as soldiers.
15 - THE BOY IN THE SUITCASE - Lene Kaaberbol
A nurse makes a shocking discovery: a naked and drugged boy hidden in a locker at the Copenhagen train station.
16 - THE ENGLISH GIRL - Daniel Silva
Gabriel Allon, an art restorer and occasional spy for the Israeli secret service, steps in to help the British prime minister, whose lover has been kidnapped.
17 - RUIN - Rachel Van Dyken
Two troubled people come together.
18 - THE KILL LIST - Frederick Forsyth
An Arabic-speaking Marine major known as the Tracker pursues a terrorist who radicalizes young Muslims living abroad.
19 - DUST - Hugh Howey
The conclusion to the Silo Saga, a series about survival in a dystopian world that began with "Wool."
Bonus: Wool Omnibus (Books 1-5) & Shift Omnibus (Books 6-8)
20 - TAMARACK COUNTY - William Kent Krueger
A private investigator pursues threats in rural Minnesota.
21 - FREEFALL - Tess Oliver
A tattoo artist finds his life disrupted when the pin-up model he s obsessed with walks into his shop.
22 - ROSE HARBOR IN BLOOM - Debbie Macomber
The second book of the Inn at Rose Harbor series continues the story of Jo Marie Rose and her bed-and-breakfast in Cedar Cove.
Bonus: Book 1 - The Inn at Rose Harbor
23 - BURN - Maya Banks
Three wealthy men explore dominance and desire.
24 - A MIND TO MURDER - P.D. James
Adam Dalgliesh of Scotland Yard investigates a murder an an upscale psychiatric clinic. Originally published in 1963.
25 - SECOND HONEYMOON - James Patterson and Howard Roughan
As he investigates the murder of a pair of newlyweds, the F.B.I. agent John O Hara, last seen in  Honeymoon  (2005), is targeted by a serial killer.
Bonus: First Book Honeymoon Included.

Authors: Various
Quantity: 25
Formats: ePUB, MOBI
Folder Size: 48.7 MB
